
'''= project to develop an open [[SIP]] Express Router'''

URL = http://www.openser.org/


=Description=

"''Robust Open Source (GPL) SIP (RFC3261) server implementation''. Among features: VoIP SIP registrar/proxy/router/application server, TLS secure communication, AAA, ENUM, LCR, load balancing, NAT traversal, OSP, CPL, SNMP, IM&Presence, DNS failover."
(http://sourceforge.net/projects/openser/)


=Technical Motivation=

"Why am I even bothering with OpenSER when there's Asterisk? Asterisk is
great, but it's not really a SIP proxy and it doesn't scale as well as
OpenSER. A single OpenSER box can handle more registrations and call
setups, than a large cluster of Asterisk boxes can at this time. This is
why Free World Dialup uses SER as it's SIP proxy and not Asterisk."
(http://www.oldskoolphreak.com/tfiles/voip/beginners_openser.txt)


